# Summit placeholder pages and `draft` status

For every new summit section (`content/<slug>/`), always create these pages:

- `summit.md`
- `agenda.md`
- `pictures.md`

If real data is not available yet, keep the placeholder pages **on-hold** by setting `draft: true` in their front matter.

## pictures.md placeholder detection

If `content/<slug>/pictures.md` only contains the placeholder text:

- `Picture gallery for MCT Summit EU <YEAR> in <City> will be published here.`

then set:

- `draft: true`

## agenda.md placeholder detection

If `content/<slug>/agenda.md` only contains placeholder content such as:

- “Full schedule not available.”
- “Session-level agenda data is not available.”
- A minimal agenda table row where `Speaker` is `—` and `Topic` contains “not available”

then set:

- `draft: true`

## summit.md draft policy

- Keep `summit.md` present for every summit.
- If `summit.md` itself is also placeholder-only (e.g., key facts like When/Where/Hosts/Title/EventSite are not known), you may also set `draft: true` for `summit.md`.

